      "title": "Expand the expression using FOIL",
      "content": "Apply FOIL to $(3x-23)(19x+6)$:<br/><ul><li><strong>First:</strong> $3x \\cdot 19x = 57x^2$</li><li><strong>Outer:</strong> $3x \\cdot 6 = 18x$</li><li><strong>Inner:</strong> $-23 \\cdot 19x = -437x$</li><li><strong>Last:</strong> $-23 \\cdot 6 = -138$</li></ul>Combining all terms:<br/>$$57x^2 + 18x - 437x - 138$$"
    },
    {
      "title": "Combine like terms to find b",
      "content": "The $x$ terms are $18x$ and $-437x$. Their sum is:<br/>$$18x - 437x = -419x$$<br/>Therefore, the expanded form is $57x^2 - 419x - 138$, which means $b = -419$."
    }
  ]
